body:
@bastiansteinert and I recently played around with the styling of windows, in particular for the SCB. 
We disabled shadows, also because we do like having less shadows in general, but this also makes interacting with windows much more pleasant. Windows react much faster, opening and moving them feels a lot more responsive, especially if there are lots of windows (or other widgets with shadows).

Here's a screenshot showing the SCB without shadows:
![scb without shadows](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/556044/818879/1689c5fa-efa3-11e2-9d93-dcb6f6e353a6.png)

If you want to see the effects for yourself, you can use the following snippet as in my *localconfig.js* (https://gist.github.com/lauritzthamsen/5999422):

```javascript
$world.setFill(Color.rgb(100,100,100));
$world.loadStyleSheetFromFile('https://gist.github.com/lauritzthamsen/5999577/raw/52b62e59d7e925fa90e459f2c4c58ac8bc333688/my_lively_preferences.css');

```

What do you think?

The width of the text node does not compensate correctly for padding.

#### Example Code

```javascript
var str = 'hmmmmmmmmmmm';
var txt = new lively.morphic.Text(lively.rect(20,10,60,50), str);
txt.openInWorld();
txt.focus();
txt.setPadding(lively.Rectangle.inset(5, 10));
```

#### Result

![paddingbug](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/479238/187103/cf7b467c-7d45-11e2-82b1-6f90d8715b0e.png)

This is work in progress and the outcome of a weekend project.

[paper.js](http://paperjs.org/) is a HTML canvas JS library that supports
vector-style canvas rendering. Since our current path / polygon implementation
that is SVG-based suffers from the issues that arise when combining SVG /
HTML, this might be a a replacement.

Usage:

```js
require('apps.paperjs').toRun(function() {
    var path = new apps.paperjs.Path([pt(0,0), pt(20,10), pt(100,100)]);
    path.openInWorld();
});
